{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1039,"text":"I cannot forget them."},{"time":3692,"text":"Their names were Aslan, Alik, Andrei,"},{"time":8469,"text":"Fernanda, Fred, Galina, Gunnhild,"},{"time":13113,"text":"Hans, Ingeborg, Matti, Natalya,"},{"time":18407,"text":"Nancy, Sheryl, Usman, Zarema,"},{"time":23167,"text":"and the list is longer."},{"time":26255,"text":"For many, their existence,\ntheir humanity,"},{"time":29599,"text":"has been reduced to statistics,"},{"time":33244,"text":"coldly recorded as \"security incidents.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":37540,"text":"For me, they were colleagues"},{"time":39095,"text":"belonging to that community\nof humanitarian aid workers"},{"time":42625,"text":"that tried to bring a bit of comfort"},{"time":45434,"text":"to the victims of the wars\nin Chechnya in the '90s."},{"time":49521,"text":"They were nurses, logisticians,\nshelter experts,"},{"time":54164,"text":"paralegals, interpreters."},{"time":56997,"text":"And for this service, they were murdered,"},{"time":61153,"text":"their families torn apart,"},{"time":63615,"text":"and their story largely forgotten."},{"time":66827,"text":"No one was ever sentenced\nfor these crimes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70884,"text":"I cannot forget them."},{"time":73041,"text":"They live in me somehow,"},{"time":75090,"text":"their memories giving me\nmeaning every day."},{"time":78320,"text":"But they are also haunting\nthe dark street of my mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82751,"text":"As humanitarian aid workers,"},{"time":84712,"text":"they made the choice\nto be at the side of the victim,"},{"time":88064,"text":"to provide some assistance,\nsome comfort, some protection,"},{"time":92661,"text":"but when they needed\nprotection themselves,"},{"time":95587,"text":"it wasn't there."},{"time":97685,"text":"When you see the headlines\nof your newspaper these days"},{"time":100858,"text":"with the war in Iraq or in Syria --"},{"time":103923,"text":"aid worker abducted, hostage executed --"},{"time":108087,"text":"but who were they?"},{"time":110100,"text":"Why were they there?"},{"time":112025,"text":"What motivated them?"},{"time":114033,"text":"How did we become\nso indifferent to these crimes?"},{"time":117909,"text":"This is why I am here today with you."},{"time":121038,"text":"We need to find better ways\nto remember them."},{"time":124575,"text":"We also need to explain the key values\nto which they dedicated their lives."},{"time":130566,"text":"We also need to demand justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136058,"text":"When in '96 I was sent"},{"time":137939,"text":"by the United Nations High Commissioner\nfor Refugees to the North Caucasus,"},{"time":141654,"text":"I knew some of the risks."},{"time":143526,"text":"Five colleagues had been killed,"},{"time":145879,"text":"three had been seriously injured,"},{"time":147946,"text":"seven had already been taken hostage."},{"time":150291,"text":"So we were careful."},{"time":152078,"text":"We were using armored \nvehicles, decoy cars,"},{"time":156152,"text":"changing patterns of travel,\nchanging homes,"},{"time":159207,"text":"all sorts of security measures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163258,"text":"Yet on a cold winter night\nof January '98, it was my turn."},{"time":169208,"text":"When I entered my flat\nin Vladikavkaz with a guard,"},{"time":173185,"text":"we were surrounded by armed men."},{"time":176781,"text":"They took the guard,\nthey put him on the floor,"},{"time":178998,"text":"they beat him up in front of me,"},{"time":181622,"text":"tied him, dragged him away."},{"time":185536,"text":"I was handcuffed, blindfolded,\nand forced to kneel,"},{"time":190321,"text":"as the silencer of a gun\npressed against my neck."},{"time":194204,"text":"When it happens to you,"},{"time":195942,"text":"there is no time for thinking,\nno time for praying."},{"time":200045,"text":"My brain went on automatic,"},{"time":202749,"text":"rewinding quickly\nthe life I'd just left behind."},{"time":207115,"text":"It took me long minutes to figure out"},{"time":209645,"text":"that those masked men there\nwere not there to kill me,"},{"time":213058,"text":"but that someone, somewhere,\nhad ordered my kidnapping."},{"time":218551,"text":"Then a process of dehumanization\nstarted that day."},{"time":222622,"text":"I was no more than just a commodity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229195,"text":"I normally don't talk about this,"},{"time":231011,"text":"but I'd like to share a bit with you\nsome of those 317 days of captivity."},{"time":236598,"text":"I was kept in an underground cellar,"},{"time":239654,"text":"total darkness,"},{"time":241718,"text":"for 23 hours and 45 minutes every day,"},{"time":245472,"text":"and then the guards \nwould come, normally two."},{"time":248758,"text":"They would bring a big piece of bread,"},{"time":251432,"text":"a bowl of soup, and a candle."},{"time":255206,"text":"That candle would burn for 15 minutes,"},{"time":259280,"text":"15 minutes of precious light,"},{"time":263088,"text":"and then they would take it away,\nand I returned to darkness."},{"time":269024,"text":"I was chained by a metal cable to my bed."},{"time":272538,"text":"I could do only four small steps."},{"time":276950,"text":"I always dreamt of the fifth one."},{"time":280735,"text":"And no TV, no radio,\nno newspaper, no one to talk to."},{"time":284976,"text":"I had no towel, no soap, no toilet paper,"},{"time":289069,"text":"just two metal buckets open,\none for water, for one waste."},{"time":297926,"text":"Can you imagine that mock execution\ncan be a pastime for guards"},{"time":302955,"text":"when they are sadistic\nor when they are just bored or drunk?"},{"time":309665,"text":"We are breaking my nerves very slowly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313073,"text":"Isolation and darkness\nare particularly difficult to describe."},{"time":317583,"text":"How do you describe nothing?"},{"time":319975,"text":"There are no words for the depths\nof loneliness I reached"},{"time":322993,"text":"in that very thin border\nbetween sanity and madness."},{"time":330168,"text":"In the darkness, sometimes\nI played imaginary games of checkers."},{"time":335408,"text":"I would start with the black,"},{"time":337611,"text":"play with the white,"},{"time":339270,"text":"back to the black\ntrying to trick the other side."},{"time":343469,"text":"I don't play checkers anymore."},{"time":346860,"text":"I was tormented by the thoughts of my\nfamily and my colleague, the guard, Edik."},{"time":353177,"text":"I didn't know what had happened to him."},{"time":355987,"text":"I was trying not to think,"},{"time":358472,"text":"I tried to fill up my time"},{"time":359932,"text":"by doing all sorts of physical\nexercise on the spot."},{"time":363743,"text":"I tried to pray, I tried all sorts\nof memorization games."},{"time":369063,"text":"But darkness also creates images\nand thoughts that are not normal."},{"time":373456,"text":"One part of your brain wants you\nto resist, to shout, to cry,"},{"time":379717,"text":"and the other part of the brain\norders you to shut up"},{"time":383154,"text":"and just go through it."},{"time":385963,"text":"It's a constant internal debate;\nthere is no one to arbitrate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391163,"text":"Once a guard came to me,\nvery aggressively, and he told me,"},{"time":396083,"text":"\"Today you're going to kneel\nand beg for your food.\""},{"time":400220,"text":"I wasn't in a good mood,\nso I insulted him."},{"time":403842,"text":"I insulted his mother,\nI insulted his ancestors."},{"time":406776,"text":"The consequence was moderate:\nhe threw the food into my waste."},{"time":411207,"text":"The day after he came back\nwith the same demand."},{"time":414882,"text":"He got the same answer,"},{"time":417321,"text":"which had the same consequence."},{"time":421532,"text":"Four days later,\nthe body was full of pain."},{"time":425363,"text":"I didn't know hunger hurt so much\nwhen you have so little."},{"time":429705,"text":"So when the guards came down,"},{"time":436049,"text":"I knelt."},{"time":439063,"text":"I begged for my food."},{"time":442081,"text":"Submission was the only way for me\nto make it to another candle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449302,"text":"After my kidnapping,"},{"time":451113,"text":"I was transferred\nfrom North Ossetia to Chechnya,"},{"time":454270,"text":"three days of slow travel\nin the trunks of different cars,"},{"time":458590,"text":"and upon arrival, I was interrogated"},{"time":460889,"text":"for 11 days by a guy called Ruslan."},{"time":464554,"text":"The routine was always the same:"},{"time":466318,"text":"a bit more light, 45 minutes."},{"time":468710,"text":"He would come down to the cellar,"},{"time":470985,"text":"he would ask the guards\nto tie me on the chair,"},{"time":473249,"text":"and he would turn on the music loud."},{"time":476349,"text":"And then he would yell questions."},{"time":479530,"text":"He would scream. He would beat me."},{"time":482325,"text":"I'll spare you the details."},{"time":484248,"text":"There are many questions\nI could not understand,"},{"time":486681,"text":"and there are some questions\nI did not want to understand."},{"time":492254,"text":"The length of the interrogation\nwas the duration of the tape:"},{"time":496433,"text":"15 songs, 45 minutes."},{"time":499800,"text":"I would always long for the last song."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502575,"text":"On one day, one night in that cellar,\nI don't know what it was,"},{"time":506280,"text":"I heard a child crying above my head,"},{"time":509297,"text":"a boy, maybe two or three years old."},{"time":512129,"text":"Footsteps, confusion, people running."},{"time":516866,"text":"So when Ruslan came the day after,"},{"time":519900,"text":"before he put the first question to me,"},{"time":522369,"text":"I asked him, \"How is your son today?\nIs he feeling better?\""},{"time":525968,"text":"Ruslan was taken by surprise."},{"time":528754,"text":"He was furious that the guards\nmay have leaked some details"},{"time":531583,"text":"about his private life."},{"time":534161,"text":"I kept talking about NGOs\nsupplying medicines to local clinics"},{"time":538874,"text":"that may help his son to get better."},{"time":541785,"text":"And we talked about education,\nwe talked about families."},{"time":545909,"text":"He talked to me about his children."},{"time":547767,"text":"I talked to him about my daughters."},{"time":549833,"text":"And then he'd talk about guns,\nabout cars, about women,"},{"time":553223,"text":"and I had to talk about guns,\nabout cars, about women."},{"time":557542,"text":"And we talked until\nthe last song on the tape."},{"time":561280,"text":"Ruslan was the most brutal man I ever met."},{"time":566923,"text":"He did not touch me anymore."},{"time":570220,"text":"He did not ask any other questions."},{"time":572936,"text":"I was no longer just a commodity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576791,"text":"Two days after, I was transferred\nto another place."},{"time":581760,"text":"There, a guard came to me,\nvery close -- it was quite unusual --"},{"time":586866,"text":"and he said with\na very soft voice, he said,"},{"time":590025,"text":"\"I'd like to thank you"},{"time":592649,"text":"for the assistance your organization\nprovided my family"},{"time":596689,"text":"when we were displaced\nin nearby Dagestan.\""},{"time":602308,"text":"What could I possibly reply?"},{"time":605891,"text":"It was so painful.\nIt was like a blade in the belly."},{"time":610667,"text":"It took me weeks of internal thinking\nto try to reconcile"},{"time":614011,"text":"the good reasons we had\nto assist that family"},{"time":617285,"text":"and the soldier of fortune he became."},{"time":620257,"text":"He was young, he was shy."},{"time":622370,"text":"I never saw his face."},{"time":624645,"text":"He probably meant well."},{"time":627315,"text":"But in those 15 seconds,"},{"time":629707,"text":"he made me question everything we did,"},{"time":633422,"text":"all the sacrifices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635813,"text":"He made me think also how they see us."},{"time":639366,"text":"Until then, I had assumed\nthat they know why we are there"},{"time":642036,"text":"and what we are doing."},{"time":644915,"text":"One cannot assume this."},{"time":647768,"text":"Well, explaining why we do this\nis not that easy,"},{"time":652020,"text":"even to our closest relatives."},{"time":655062,"text":"We are not perfect, we are not superior,"},{"time":658459,"text":"we are not the world's fire brigade,"},{"time":660935,"text":"we are not superheroes,"},{"time":663049,"text":"we don't stop wars,"},{"time":664721,"text":"we know that humanitarian response is not\na substitute for political solution."},{"time":670105,"text":"Yet we do this because one life matters."},{"time":674563,"text":"Sometimes that's the only\ndifference you make --"},{"time":676816,"text":"one individual, one family,\na small group of individuals --"},{"time":680136,"text":"and it matters."},{"time":682110,"text":"When you have a tsunami,\nan earthquake or a typhoon,"},{"time":684967,"text":"you see teams of rescuers\ncoming from all over the world,"},{"time":689075,"text":"searching for survivors for weeks."},{"time":692117,"text":"Why? Nobody questions this."},{"time":694671,"text":"Every life matters,"},{"time":696784,"text":"or every life should matter."},{"time":701010,"text":"This is the same for us\nwhen we help refugees,"},{"time":703935,"text":"people displaced within their country\nby conflict, or stateless persons,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":709595,"text":"I know many people,"},{"time":711390,"text":"when they are confronted\nby overwhelming suffering,"},{"time":714398,"text":"they feel powerless and they stop there."},{"time":718169,"text":"It's a pity, because there are\nso many ways people can help."},{"time":722046,"text":"We don't stop with that feeling."},{"time":724027,"text":"We try to do whatever we can\nto provide some assistance,"},{"time":726678,"text":"some protection, some comfort."},{"time":729332,"text":"We have to."},{"time":731093,"text":"We can't do otherwise."},{"time":732843,"text":"It's what makes us feel,\nI don't know, simply human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738197,"text":"That's a picture of me\nthe day of my release."},{"time":742316,"text":"Months after my release,\nI met the then-French prime minister."},{"time":746658,"text":"The second thing he told me:"},{"time":748700,"text":"\"You were totally irresponsible\nto go to the North Caucasus."},{"time":752231,"text":"You don't know how many\nproblems you've created for us.\""},{"time":758017,"text":"It was a short meeting."},{"time":759852,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":762661,"text":"I think helping people\nin danger is responsible."},{"time":767235,"text":"In that war, that nobody\nseriously wanted to stop,"},{"time":771763,"text":"and we have many of these today,"},{"time":774108,"text":"bringing some assistance to people in need\nand a bit of protection"},{"time":778608,"text":"was not just an act of humanity,"},{"time":780517,"text":"it was making a real difference\nfor the people."},{"time":783419,"text":"Why could he not understand this?"},{"time":786670,"text":"We have a responsibility to try."},{"time":788597,"text":"You've heard about that concept:\nResponsibility to Protect."},{"time":792431,"text":"Outcomes may depend\non various parameters."},{"time":796512,"text":"We may even fail,\nbut there is worse than failing --"},{"time":800369,"text":"it's not even trying when we can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804441,"text":"Well, if you are met this way,\nif you sign up for this sort of job,"},{"time":808316,"text":"your life is going to be full\nof joy and sadness,"},{"time":812954,"text":"because there are a lot of people\nwe cannot help,"},{"time":815633,"text":"a lot of people we cannot protect,\na lot of people we did not save."},{"time":819557,"text":"I call them my ghost,"},{"time":821800,"text":"and by having witnessed\ntheir suffering from close,"},{"time":824757,"text":"you take a bit \nof that suffering on yourself."},{"time":829304,"text":"Many young humanitarian workers"},{"time":831970,"text":"go through their first experience\nwith a lot of bitterness."},{"time":834988,"text":"They are thrown into situations\nwhere they are witness,"},{"time":837960,"text":"but they are powerless\nto bring any change."},{"time":841072,"text":"They have to learn to accept it"},{"time":843579,"text":"and gradually turn this\ninto positive energy."},{"time":846958,"text":"It's difficult."},{"time":848407,"text":"Many don't succeed,"},{"time":850945,"text":"but for those who do,\nthere is no other job like this."},{"time":854953,"text":"You can see the difference\nyou make every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859643,"text":"Humanitarian aid workers\nknow the risk they are taking"},{"time":862805,"text":"in conflict areas or \nin post-conflict environments,"},{"time":867717,"text":"yet our life, our job, is becoming \nincreasingly life-threatening,"},{"time":874429,"text":"and the sanctity of our life is fading."},{"time":879441,"text":"Do you know that since the millennium,"},{"time":882100,"text":"the number of attacks on humanitarian \naid workers has tripled?"},{"time":887409,"text":"2013 broke new records:"},{"time":891111,"text":"155 colleagues killed,"},{"time":894383,"text":"171 seriously wounded,"},{"time":897517,"text":"134 abducted."},{"time":901375,"text":"So many broken lives."},{"time":905178,"text":"Until the beginning of the civil war\nin Somalia in the late '80s,"},{"time":910380,"text":"humanitarian aid workers\nwere sometimes victims"},{"time":914490,"text":"of what we call collateral damages,"},{"time":916487,"text":"but by and large we were not\nthe target of these attacks."},{"time":920202,"text":"This has changed."},{"time":921756,"text":"Look at this picture."},{"time":923032,"text":"Baghdad, August 2003:"},{"time":925866,"text":"24 colleagues were killed."},{"time":928631,"text":"Gone are the days when\na U.N. blue flag or a Red Cross"},{"time":932157,"text":"would automatically protect us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935933,"text":"Criminal groups and some political groups"},{"time":939195,"text":"have cross-fertilized\nover the last 20 years,"},{"time":942051,"text":"and they've created these sort of hybrids"},{"time":945186,"text":"with whom we have no way of communicating."},{"time":948052,"text":"Humanitarian principles are tested,\nquestioned, and often ignored,"},{"time":953426,"text":"but perhaps more importantly,\nwe have abandoned the search for justice."},{"time":958312,"text":"There seems to be\nno consequence whatsoever"},{"time":961532,"text":"for attacks against\nhumanitarian aid workers."},{"time":964997,"text":"After my release, I was told\nnot to seek any form of justice."},{"time":969357,"text":"It won't do you any good,\nthat's what I was told."},{"time":972584,"text":"Plus, you're going to put in danger\nthe life of other colleagues."},{"time":977723,"text":"It took me years to see the sentencing"}]},{"cues":[{"time":980884,"text":"of three people associated \nwith my kidnapping,"},{"time":985175,"text":"but this was the exception."},{"time":987711,"text":"There was no justice for any \nof the humanitarian aid workers"},{"time":992230,"text":"killed or abducted in Chechnya\nbetween '95 and '99,"},{"time":996518,"text":"and it's the same all over the world."},{"time":1000436,"text":"This is unacceptable."},{"time":1002583,"text":"This is inexcusable."},{"time":1004394,"text":"Attacks on humanitarian aid workers\nare war crimes in international law."},{"time":1009107,"text":"Those crimes should not go unpunished."},{"time":1012195,"text":"We must end this cycle of impunity."},{"time":1014935,"text":"We must consider that those attacks\nagainst humanitarian aid workers"},{"time":1018766,"text":"are attacks against humanity itself."},{"time":1022319,"text":"That makes me furious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026274,"text":"I know I'm very lucky\ncompared to the refugees I work for."},{"time":1032414,"text":"I don't know what it is to have seen\nmy whole town destroyed."},{"time":1036041,"text":"I don't know what it is to have seen\nmy relatives shot in front of me."},{"time":1040105,"text":"I don't know what it is to lose\nthe protection of my country."},{"time":1044354,"text":"I also know that I'm very lucky\ncompared to other hostages."},{"time":1048649,"text":"Four days before my eventful release,\nfour hostages were beheaded"},{"time":1054331,"text":"a few miles away from where\nI was kept in captivity."},{"time":1058726,"text":"Why them?"},{"time":1060930,"text":"Why am I here today?"},{"time":1064641,"text":"No easy answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068430,"text":"I was received with a lot of support\nthat I got from my relatives,"},{"time":1072043,"text":"from colleagues, from friends,\nfrom people I didn't know."},{"time":1075862,"text":"They have helped me over the years\nto come out of the darkness."},{"time":1080291,"text":"Not everyone was treated\nwith the same attention."},{"time":1084189,"text":"How many of my colleagues,\nafter a traumatic incident,"},{"time":1087814,"text":"took their own life?"},{"time":1091090,"text":"I can count nine that I knew personally."},{"time":1094819,"text":"How many of my colleagues\nwent through a difficult divorce"},{"time":1098547,"text":"after a traumatic experience"},{"time":1101481,"text":"because they could not explain\nanything anymore to their spouse?"},{"time":1106209,"text":"I've lost that count."},{"time":1108663,"text":"There is a price for this type of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1112223,"text":"In Russia, all war monuments have\nthis beautiful inscription at the top."},{"time":1116856,"text":"It says, (In Russian)"},{"time":1120965,"text":"\"No one is forgotten,\nnothing is forgotten.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1125386,"text":"I do not forget my lost colleagues."},{"time":1128523,"text":"I cannot forget anything."},{"time":1130859,"text":"I call on you to remember their dedication"},{"time":1134072,"text":"and demand that humanitarian\naid workers around the world"},{"time":1137578,"text":"be better protected."},{"time":1140155,"text":"We should not let that light of hope\nthey have brought to be switched off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1145751,"text":"After my ordeal, a lot of colleagues\nasked me, \"But why do you continue?"},{"time":1150441,"text":"Why do you do this sort of job?"},{"time":1152647,"text":"Why do you have to go back to it?\""},{"time":1155201,"text":"My answer was very simple:"},{"time":1158066,"text":"If I had quit,"},{"time":1160536,"text":"that would have meant\nmy kidnapper had won."},{"time":1164553,"text":"They would have taken my soul"},{"time":1166904,"text":"and my humanity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1169179,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1171826,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}